  "notes": [
    {
      "type": "Research Gap",
      "text": "\n               \u003cxhtml:p\u003eSymlink vulnerabilities are regularly found in C and shell programs, but all programming languages can have this problem. Even shell programs are probably under-reported.\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n               \u003cxhtml:p\u003e\"Second-order symlink vulnerabilities\" may exist in programs that invoke other programs that follow symlinks. They are rarely reported but are likely to be fairly common when process invocation is used [REF-493].\u003c/xhtml:p\u003e\n            "
    }
